 of the work of these artists attests to a performative turn in Latin American art during the 1980s that, like photography and film before, recast the artistic field as a whole, changing the ways in which we perceive art and understand its role in society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aArt and societyzLatin AmericaxHistoryy20th century. 0aArtxPolitical aspectszLatin AmericaxHistoryy20th century. 0aBody artzLatin America. 0aPerformance artzLatin America. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831106535260 cprintz978197880202540uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9781978802063?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978802063423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978802063/original  a978-3-11-065352-6  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK